# AVPlayerItemMetadataOutputPushDelegate

**Protocol**

Methods you can implement to provide additional metadata.

## Declaration

```swift
protocol AVPlayerItemMetadataOutputPushDelegate : AVPlayerItemOutputPushDelegate
```

## Overview

This protocol extends the [doc://com.apple.avfoundation/documentation/AVFoundation/AVPlayerItemOutputPushDelegate] protocol.

## Combining timed metadata groups

- **metadataOutput(_:didOutputTimedMetadataGroups:from:)**: Tells the delegate a new collection of metadata items is available.

## Configuring the delegate

- **advanceIntervalForDelegateInvocation**: The time interval, in seconds, the player item metadata output object messages its delegate earlier than normal.
- **delegate**: The delegate object.
- **delegateQueue**: The dispatch queue on which messages are sent to the delegate.
- **setDelegate(_:queue:)**: Sets the delegate and a dispatch queue on which the delegate is called.

- AVPlayerItemOutputPushDelegate
